WEBVTT

00:04.070 --> 00:07.172
Think of your worst pain
and then stretch it out

00:07.174 --> 00:10.042
over day in and day out
every day.

00:16.182 --> 00:17.549
[woman 1 tearfully]
<i>Somewhere in me is this</i>

00:17.551 --> 00:19.885
<i>little glimmer of hope.</i>

00:19.887 --> 00:22.221
<i>I just want to be
a normal person.</i>

00:22.223 --> 00:23.255
[groans softly]

00:23.790 --> 00:25.457
[panting]

00:33.199 --> 00:34.133
<i>[man 1] You can't do it</i>

00:34.135 --> 00:36.268
and then I just get mad.

00:36.270 --> 00:38.137
<i>[woman 2] If I don't make
a change now</i>

00:38.139 --> 00:39.571
<i>I'm scared it's gonna
be too late.</i>

00:43.910 --> 00:45.644
[moaning]

00:45.646 --> 00:46.845
It hurts.

00:46.847 --> 00:49.148
<i>[woman 3] I refuse
to stop fighting.</i>

00:49.150 --> 00:51.283
<i>I have to do this
for my children.</i>

00:57.323 --> 01:00.059
This is a very dangerous
situation you are in

01:00.061 --> 01:02.027
and God knows if you're gonna

01:02.029 --> 01:03.562
survive four months.

01:19.079 --> 01:21.513
[slow instrumental
music playing]

01:36.830 --> 01:39.198
[Ontreon Shannon] <i>The first
thing that comes to my mind is,</i>

01:39.200 --> 01:42.234
<i>"Am I fighting
a losing a battle?</i>

01:42.236 --> 01:45.070
<i>Because of the medical issues
that I have."</i>

01:45.772 --> 01:48.006
<i>I have congestive heart failure</i>

01:48.008 --> 01:50.576
<i>and I'm in advanced stages
of diabetes.</i>

01:51.845 --> 01:54.079
<i>I have two or three different
doctors that said</i>

01:54.081 --> 01:56.982
<i>I would be lucky to even see 40.</i>

01:57.717 --> 02:00.119
<i>The worst is already beginning
to happen.</i>

02:00.720 --> 02:03.122
<i>It's definitely no way to live.</i>

02:07.093 --> 02:10.162
<i>I take about
13 to 14 different medications</i>

02:10.164 --> 02:12.297
<i>to make sure my heart
does not fail.</i>

02:12.299 --> 02:15.501
<i>And that's the only thing that
keeps me out of the hospital.</i>

02:19.272 --> 02:22.174
<i>Being this big is horrible.</i>

02:22.176 --> 02:24.009
<i>Think of your worst pain</i>

02:24.677 --> 02:26.912
and then stretch it out

02:26.914 --> 02:29.948
over day in and day out
every day.

02:29.950 --> 02:32.551
Some days it's hard for me
to even get out of bed.

02:32.553 --> 02:34.119
<i>But I gotta keep moving.</i>

02:34.121 --> 02:36.221
<i>I have a wife to take care of.</i>

02:36.223 --> 02:39.791
<i>I have a mother to help out
as much as I can.</i>

02:39.793 --> 02:41.960
<i>Just in the last month,</i>

02:41.962 --> 02:45.797
<i>recently due to
my health concerns,</i>

02:45.799 --> 02:47.032
<i>me and my wife...</i>

02:47.034 --> 02:49.134
<i>I have moved in with my mom,</i>

02:49.136 --> 02:52.738
<i>got to the point to where there
are things that I need help with.</i>

02:52.740 --> 02:55.240
<i>It's just to much for Musa
to do to help</i>

02:55.242 --> 02:57.809
provide what is needed
and that's...

02:57.811 --> 03:00.312
It'll just make you feel uneasy.

03:02.015 --> 03:04.816
<i>I don't like to burden
my wife, Nothabo,</i>

03:04.818 --> 03:06.985
<i>to come and help me
with everything.</i>

03:07.754 --> 03:10.155
<i>So I've had to really
plan out, you know?</i>

03:11.024 --> 03:12.824
<i>Whatever I try to do on my own,</i>

03:12.826 --> 03:14.593
<i>I do very carefully.</i>

03:20.500 --> 03:23.435
<i>I usually do what I call
a pre-wash.</i>

03:24.771 --> 03:27.806
<i>I just try
to put soap everywhere</i>

03:27.808 --> 03:30.375
<i>and wash really good
from a sit down position</i>

03:30.643 --> 03:32.177
<i>outside the tub.</i>

03:33.880 --> 03:37.749
<i>And then usually I get
inside the shower to rinse off.</i>

03:37.751 --> 03:39.551
<i>And the reason why
I do it that way</i>

03:39.553 --> 03:43.055
<i>is because I can only stand up
for about five minutes,</i>

03:43.057 --> 03:46.258
<i>and I have slipped
and fallen in the tub before.</i>

03:47.060 --> 03:50.128
<i>So I try to take
as much measures</i>

03:50.130 --> 03:53.198
<i>to prevent a fall
as much as possible</i>

03:53.200 --> 03:55.067
<i>and not to overdo it.</i>

03:57.036 --> 03:59.238
<i>I usually don't shower by myself</i>

03:59.240 --> 04:02.307
<i>unless my wife or my mom
are close enough to hear me.</i>

04:02.309 --> 04:04.376
<i>If I need to call out for help.</i>

04:07.247 --> 04:09.248
<i>After I finish taking a shower</i>

04:09.250 --> 04:11.183
<i>I'm ready to lay back down.</i>

04:11.851 --> 04:13.919
<i>Not necessarily go back to bed</i>

04:13.921 --> 04:15.454
<i>but I have to rest.</i>

04:18.024 --> 04:20.559
<i>You know, just because
to go take a shower</i>

04:20.561 --> 04:23.028
<i>that takes away
all of my energy.</i>

04:24.664 --> 04:28.734
<i>I'm simply just not able
to move like I used to.</i>

04:28.736 --> 04:31.470
<i>Even just getting dressed
and stuff like that.</i>

04:32.338 --> 04:34.473
<i>There's a challenge
on every end.</i>

04:41.180 --> 04:42.881
Hey, you going to make lunch?

04:42.883 --> 04:45.350
Uh-huh. What do you want
to have for lunch?

04:45.352 --> 04:46.952
- Pizza.
- [Musa laughs]

04:46.954 --> 04:48.220
But you know what?

04:48.554 --> 04:51.556
I'm gonna make fish.

04:51.558 --> 04:53.992
- And some rice?
- [Musa] Rice?

04:53.994 --> 04:56.228
I'm not gonna make the rice
like Mommy does,

04:56.230 --> 04:58.163
with butter and stuff.

04:58.165 --> 04:58.997
I'm not gonna do that.

04:58.999 --> 05:00.365
Well, baby, okay.

05:00.367 --> 05:03.101
Well, baby, why don't we put
some of that cheese on there?

05:03.103 --> 05:05.270
- On rice.
- No, no, no, no.

05:07.173 --> 05:09.841
<i>[Ontreon] My relationship
with food is definitely</i>

05:09.843 --> 05:12.311
<i>a very unhealthy relationship.</i>

05:12.845 --> 05:15.047
<i>But with all my health issues</i>

05:15.049 --> 05:17.949
<i>and just the pain
that it takes for me to do</i>

05:17.951 --> 05:20.886
<i>the most basic daily function,</i>

05:20.888 --> 05:24.589
<i>I am always overwhelmed
and highly stressed,</i>

05:24.591 --> 05:27.092
<i>and food is how I process that.</i>

05:27.360 --> 05:28.994
<i>I can comfort myself</i>

05:28.996 --> 05:31.330
<i>from the stress and the exertion</i>

05:31.332 --> 05:34.599
<i>and enjoy a moment
not dealing with all that.</i>

05:35.935 --> 05:38.003
<i>But on bad days
the overwhelmingness</i>

05:38.005 --> 05:39.938
<i>is a bottomless pit.</i>

05:39.940 --> 05:42.040
<i>So I eat and try to forget
about my life</i>

05:42.042 --> 05:44.676
<i>and all the things
that I've been through.</i>

05:44.678 --> 05:47.379
<i>It seems like there's
so many things to forget.</i>

05:48.981 --> 05:51.116
I come from
a single parent home.

05:51.150 --> 05:52.951
<i>I did know my father</i>

05:52.953 --> 05:55.287
<i>but he was still
not in the household.</i>

05:55.289 --> 05:57.756
<i>So I was raised by my mother</i>

05:57.758 --> 05:59.991
<i>and she made sure that</i>

05:59.993 --> 06:01.793
as I child I didn't want
for anything.

06:01.795 --> 06:04.062
<i>And I didn't realize until</i>

06:04.064 --> 06:06.498
<i>my later teenage years,
she struggled.</i>

06:07.100 --> 06:08.633
If Mom had to work two jobs

06:08.635 --> 06:10.268
she would just went
and worked two jobs.

06:10.270 --> 06:13.004
If she had to work three jobs,
well, that's what she did.

06:13.039 --> 06:16.074
<i>My siblings were with our dad.</i>

06:16.076 --> 06:19.845
<i>So I was the only one that was in
the house while Mom was working.</i>

06:19.847 --> 06:21.947
<i>But my grandparents,
at the time,</i>

06:21.949 --> 06:25.016
<i>my grandmother, she was retired,</i>

06:25.018 --> 06:27.219
<i>and so I spent a lot of times
there with her.</i>

06:27.221 --> 06:29.287
And what do we do? We eat.

06:29.289 --> 06:31.156
We play games, but we eat.

06:31.158 --> 06:32.991
We do this, but we eat.

06:32.993 --> 06:34.326
And so food

06:34.328 --> 06:36.561
and good food
was always present.

06:38.765 --> 06:40.932
How many calories is that?

06:40.934 --> 06:44.202
- What you're supposed to eat.
- [both laugh]

06:45.238 --> 06:46.338
You gonna put some honey on it?

06:46.340 --> 06:49.408
Oh. [laughs] Cinnamon.

06:49.842 --> 06:51.543
We was a church going family.

06:51.545 --> 06:55.046
My grandparents and my mother
definitely kept me in church a lot.

06:55.048 --> 06:59.050
<i>Every Sunday we can guarantee
that we was there at church,</i>

06:59.052 --> 07:02.554
<i>and so that was a good thing,
it helped me stay grounded.</i>

07:03.656 --> 07:05.957
Food was just a big thing
in our home.

07:05.959 --> 07:08.960
My mom was a cook,
my aunties are cooks.

07:08.962 --> 07:11.863
<i>We celebrated with eating</i>

07:11.865 --> 07:14.099
<i>everywhere we went,
church meals.</i>

07:14.567 --> 07:15.934
<i>I worked a lot.</i>

07:16.035 --> 07:17.202
<i>He was home a lot.</i>

07:17.204 --> 07:20.038
I worked a lot,
he was at my parent's a lot.

07:20.040 --> 07:21.840
<i>He got everything he wanted</i>

07:21.842 --> 07:23.575
<i>and some he didn't want.</i>

07:23.577 --> 07:26.711
<i>So, yeah, I think
that's what started...</i>

07:26.713 --> 07:28.780
<i>I, I just think
that he was available</i>

07:28.782 --> 07:31.383
to everything he wanted
whenever he wanted it.

07:33.019 --> 07:34.686
[Ontreon]
<i>In elementary school,</i>

07:34.688 --> 07:37.689
<i>I was 20, 30 pounds overweight,</i>

07:37.691 --> 07:40.725
<i>you know, nothing that no one
really noticed.</i>

07:40.727 --> 07:42.961
<i>But it definitely became
more of a issue</i>

07:42.963 --> 07:45.564
in middle school,
around the 7th grade area,

07:45.566 --> 07:47.566
<i>because when I was 12</i>

07:47.568 --> 07:50.569
<i>my grandfather up
and had a stroke and died.</i>

07:50.571 --> 07:53.538
<i>And food definitely became
more of a comfort.</i>

07:53.540 --> 07:55.106
So dealing with
the grief of that

07:55.108 --> 07:58.844
instead of reaching
to other sources

07:58.846 --> 08:00.011
<i>I kind of let all that go.</i>

08:00.013 --> 08:03.782
<i>To try to fill a void
that you can't fill with food.</i>

08:03.784 --> 08:07.285
<i>And so that's when I started really
noticing that was an issue at school.</i>

08:08.721 --> 08:11.823
<i>Then my estranged father died
of a heart attack.</i>

08:11.825 --> 08:14.826
<i>And even though I never spent
any time with him</i>

08:14.828 --> 08:16.561
<i>I was overwhelmed with grief.</i>

08:16.563 --> 08:18.396
The lack of care,

08:18.698 --> 08:20.031
I became present

08:20.099 --> 08:24.002
and then so definitely the
weight added on quickly after that.

08:24.871 --> 08:26.104
Lord, bless this food

08:26.272 --> 08:27.906
let it be nourishing to our
bodies in the name of Jesus.

08:27.908 --> 08:29.207
Bless the hands that made it.

08:29.209 --> 08:31.109
Lord, we thank you
for all that you have done.

08:31.111 --> 08:32.577
In Jesus' name. Amen.

08:32.579 --> 08:33.578
Amen.

08:35.014 --> 08:36.848
<i>[Ontreon] And by the time
I turned 18,</i>

08:36.850 --> 08:39.551
<i>my weight was around 450 pounds.</i>

08:39.553 --> 08:42.988
<i>I ended up dropping out
of college after one semester.</i>

08:42.990 --> 08:46.157
<i>I got a job working
in security at a retail store.</i>

08:46.859 --> 08:48.059
<i>The job paid well.</i>

08:48.061 --> 08:49.661
<i>For seven years</i>

08:49.663 --> 08:52.664
<i>working ten to 14-hour days.</i>

08:52.666 --> 08:55.901
<i>At first my size worked
in my favor.</i>

08:55.903 --> 08:58.737
<i>Being big helped
intimidate customers</i>

08:58.739 --> 09:00.939
<i>who came to steal things.</i>

09:00.941 --> 09:04.142
<i>And that's when I started to
have health issues of my own,</i>

09:04.144 --> 09:07.979
<i>and I got diagnosed
with congestive heart failure.</i>

09:07.981 --> 09:11.550
<i>And then the cardiologist
cut me off as a patient.</i>

09:11.552 --> 09:12.951
<i>And she said that there's</i>

09:12.953 --> 09:14.686
<i>nothing that we can do for you.</i>

09:14.688 --> 09:16.221
<i>I lost my job at the store,</i>

09:16.223 --> 09:18.757
<i>and had a total
mental breakdown.</i>

09:18.759 --> 09:21.126
<i>I ended up becoming suicidal.</i>

09:21.128 --> 09:23.194
<i>And then as I was making plans</i>

09:23.196 --> 09:25.564
<i>to make my ultimate escape</i>

09:25.566 --> 09:27.799
<i>from all the pain and burdens</i>

09:27.801 --> 09:29.334
<i>of my situation,</i>

09:29.336 --> 09:31.670
<i>all of a sudden
there was a inner peace</i>

09:31.672 --> 09:33.438
<i>that I surrendered to.</i>

09:33.440 --> 09:36.875
<i>It was like God was saying,
"I got you."</i>

09:36.877 --> 09:39.210
<i>So the fact that I'm still here</i>

09:39.212 --> 09:42.113
<i>it's only because
of God's grace.</i>

09:44.083 --> 09:46.117
<i>So I made a pact with God</i>

09:46.119 --> 09:48.753
<i>to change my ways around eating.</i>

09:48.755 --> 09:51.256
<i>I found a little odd jobs
here and there</i>

09:51.258 --> 09:53.158
<i>and then I got into driving</i>

09:53.160 --> 09:55.226
<i>for ride share companies.</i>

09:56.929 --> 09:59.197
<i>That was more forgiving
on my body</i>

09:59.199 --> 10:02.100
<i>because I didn't have
to stand all day.</i>

10:02.102 --> 10:04.102
<i>I tried intermittent fasting</i>

10:04.104 --> 10:06.905
<i>and was able to lose
almost 200 pounds</i>

10:06.907 --> 10:08.573
<i>in a short amount of time.</i>

10:10.810 --> 10:13.244
<i>And this is when
I met my wife, Nothabo,</i>

10:13.246 --> 10:14.980
<i>who I call Musa.</i>

10:14.982 --> 10:17.115
Ontreon is my husband.

10:17.117 --> 10:19.250
<i>We met... He was my driver.</i>

10:19.252 --> 10:22.087
<i>I guess it was love
at first sight.</i>

10:22.788 --> 10:24.155
We got married, um...
[chuckles softly]

10:24.157 --> 10:27.058
Within a month we married.

10:27.060 --> 10:29.561
<i>He's been like this
ever since I met him.</i>

10:30.162 --> 10:32.030
<i>But the past two years,</i>

10:32.032 --> 10:33.098
he hasn't changed.

10:33.100 --> 10:34.232
So I'm doubting

10:34.234 --> 10:36.234
<i>if he loses that weight.</i>

10:40.006 --> 10:41.373
<i>[Ontreon] We have been
going strong</i>

10:41.375 --> 10:43.141
<i>over two years.</i>

10:43.143 --> 10:44.643
<i>But at the same time</i>

10:44.645 --> 10:46.878
<i>I began gaining weight</i>

10:46.880 --> 10:49.247
<i>and then it just gradually
kept going up.</i>

10:50.416 --> 10:51.983
You know what
the rice is missing?

10:52.351 --> 10:53.118
Butter?

10:53.120 --> 10:54.986
- You bet ya.
- No.

10:54.988 --> 10:57.422
- I'm not going to be doing that kind of rice.
- [Ontreon laughs]

10:59.992 --> 11:01.993
<i>[Ontreon] I do thank God that</i>

11:01.995 --> 11:04.462
<i>I do have a wife
that is willing to be there</i>

11:04.897 --> 11:05.930
<i>to help me out.</i>

11:08.134 --> 11:10.568
<i>[Musa] When I met him
he was moving around.</i>

11:10.570 --> 11:13.004
<i>I saw that he was willing
to change</i>

11:13.006 --> 11:15.006
<i>and so I gave him</i>

11:15.008 --> 11:16.241
<i>a chance.</i>

11:16.809 --> 11:18.610
But now he wants a family.

11:18.612 --> 11:20.979
I cannot give it to him unless

11:20.981 --> 11:23.948
<i>he loses that weight
so that we help each other.</i>

11:25.551 --> 11:27.118
You done?

11:27.120 --> 11:29.054
- [Ontreon] Thank you, baby doll.
- [Musa] Oh.

11:29.355 --> 11:31.156
It was really actually good.

11:31.158 --> 11:32.490
Compliments to the chef.

11:32.925 --> 11:34.025
Mmm.

11:34.794 --> 11:36.027
[Ontreon laughs]

11:45.071 --> 11:46.871
<i>[Ontreon] Every time we go out</i>

11:46.873 --> 11:48.139
<i>I can do less</i>

11:48.507 --> 11:50.275
<i>in how far I can go.</i>

11:50.277 --> 11:52.243
<i>Gets shorter and shorter.</i>

11:53.045 --> 11:55.180
<i>And I feel a short of breath</i>

11:55.182 --> 11:57.248
<i>before I can even make it
to the door.</i>

12:07.193 --> 12:09.761
<i>My wife understands that</i>

12:09.763 --> 12:12.964
sometimes I struggle
with the bad choices of food.

12:13.866 --> 12:14.999
Oh, we should get two of this.

12:15.001 --> 12:16.201
[Musa laughs]

12:16.836 --> 12:17.535
[Musa] No, just one.

12:18.237 --> 12:19.270
I'm taking...

12:19.272 --> 12:20.438
[Ontreon] No, you're not.

12:21.240 --> 12:22.307
[Musa] It's good for you, Tron.

12:22.309 --> 12:23.975
[Ontreon] You need
to put that back.

12:24.410 --> 12:25.677
We don't eat rabbit food.

12:25.679 --> 12:26.811
We're moving.

12:28.681 --> 12:31.783
<i>She's been watching out
and she wants me healthy.</i>

12:31.785 --> 12:33.785
<i>She wants me here for,
for a while</i>

12:33.787 --> 12:35.019
<i>and I understand that.</i>

12:35.888 --> 12:37.021
[Ontreon speaking]

12:39.291 --> 12:41.326
[Musa speaking]

12:45.097 --> 12:46.397
- The chair?
- Yeah.

13:01.313 --> 13:03.248
<i>[Ontreon] I, literally,
let my weight</i>

13:03.582 --> 13:05.150
<i>drag our lives down.</i>

13:05.551 --> 13:07.252
<i>Down to where I'm at now.</i>

13:07.887 --> 13:09.954
We never got a honeymoon.

13:09.956 --> 13:12.657
<i>Places that she wanna go
and I would like to go.</i>

13:12.659 --> 13:14.159
<i>She wanted to have children.</i>

13:14.161 --> 13:16.861
<i>We can't produce any right now
at this size.</i>

13:16.863 --> 13:18.963
<i>I feel, uh, frustrated</i>

13:18.965 --> 13:20.165
<i>and angry because,</i>

13:20.167 --> 13:22.367
<i>um, I can't provide
those things for her.</i>

13:22.369 --> 13:25.203
The best thing that I can do
is to get healthier

13:25.205 --> 13:27.038
the best way that I can.

13:28.974 --> 13:29.974
Baby, could you get the soda?

13:29.976 --> 13:31.176
[Musa grunts]

13:31.178 --> 13:33.111
Thank you, just set it...
Yeah, baby.

13:33.113 --> 13:35.079
You got the basket?

13:35.081 --> 13:36.815
- No, you take the whole basket.
- [Ontreon] Thank you, baby.

13:36.817 --> 13:39.184
- [Ontreon] Aw, you so sweet.
- Oh, please.

13:39.186 --> 13:41.152
[Ontreon]
That's a beautiful wife.

13:44.390 --> 13:46.224
- Run, Forrest.
- Woo.

13:46.226 --> 13:47.559
[Ontreon] Run, get in.

13:49.028 --> 13:51.162
[Musa speaking]

13:53.299 --> 13:54.365
[Ontreon] Ooh, baby.

13:54.967 --> 13:56.067
[Ontreon groans]

13:56.069 --> 13:57.135
[Musa speaking]

13:57.870 --> 13:58.570
[Ontreon] Yep.

13:58.572 --> 14:00.171
[Musa speaking]

