- So we doing the easy day today? Oh, no.
- [laughs]

34:38.710 --> 34:42.145
We got work to do. Let's
go. Turn it off. Let's roll.

34:42.147 --> 34:46.249
See, today we're supposed to go
easy, supposed to be a light day.

34:46.251 --> 34:48.418
-There's no such thing. Let's go.
-[laughs]

34:50.354 --> 34:54.291
<i>I wanted to wait until Charles
was available to do my first workout.</i>

34:54.293 --> 34:56.660
<i>Because I knew he was going
to make it more fun for me.</i>

34:56.662 --> 34:58.395
All right, you're pulling that.

34:58.397 --> 35:02.299
- Charles, let's cut across this grass real quick.
- [laughs]

35:02.301 --> 35:04.601
I'll pave it the whole way
so let's go.

35:05.336 --> 35:07.137
Charles, that's a long way.

35:07.438 --> 35:09.172
Let's go.

35:09.174 --> 35:11.942
<i>[Ontreon] If I didn't have somebody
like Charles to do it with me,</i>

35:11.944 --> 35:14.911
<i>it was gonna make it
a lot harder.</i>

35:14.913 --> 35:17.214
<i>The one thing that I know
that I'm not gonna like about this</i>

35:17.216 --> 35:20.784
<i>is Charles is gonna make me
go longer than I want to.</i>

35:20.786 --> 35:22.853
[Charles] We could
go around the whole lake.

35:22.855 --> 35:25.322
- No, no, no, you crazy. [laughs]
- Okay, okay. I'm just saying.

35:25.324 --> 35:27.457
Hey, that's a good looking
incline. You got one more.

35:29.127 --> 35:30.861
I'm gonna go to this corner.

35:30.863 --> 35:31.895
- Right here.
- Corner?

35:31.897 --> 35:32.762
Yup. So come on.

35:32.764 --> 35:35.265
[panting]

35:39.437 --> 35:40.937
- Don't be so eager to sit.
- [laughs]

35:40.939 --> 35:43.340
- That's the fastest you've moved all morning.
- [coughs]

35:43.342 --> 35:45.075
Huh? All right,
we're gonna need this.

35:45.077 --> 35:46.343
Let me move this out of the way.

35:47.078 --> 35:48.278
All right. So...

35:49.046 --> 35:50.947
Now you gotta sit and work.

35:50.949 --> 35:53.583
All right, so we're taking this
ball, you press it above your head.

35:53.585 --> 35:56.019
All right, here we go.
Keep pressing it straight up.

35:56.021 --> 35:58.588
Here we go. Three, two, one.
Here we go. One.

35:59.357 --> 36:02.225
Slow. Two. Three.

36:03.027 --> 36:05.162
Four. Five.

36:06.063 --> 36:08.064
Six. Seven.

36:09.066 --> 36:11.034
Eight. Nine.

36:11.903 --> 36:13.770
Ten. Nice.

36:13.772 --> 36:16.173
Nice. All right, on your feet,
here we go, we're kicking.

36:16.175 --> 36:18.575
On three, here we go.
Lift, one.

36:20.244 --> 36:21.244
Two.

36:22.079 --> 36:23.079
Three.

36:23.948 --> 36:25.115
Four.

36:25.883 --> 36:28.018
Five. All right, stand up.

36:29.220 --> 36:31.021
I'm not no Samson.

36:31.023 --> 36:33.089
[both laugh]

36:33.091 --> 36:36.526
Come on, Samson. Come
forward. All right, see right here?

36:37.395 --> 36:38.562
So you're gonna press like this.

36:39.463 --> 36:40.463
One.

36:41.365 --> 36:42.465
Two.

36:43.868 --> 36:44.935
Three. That's it.

36:45.970 --> 36:47.003
Four.

36:47.605 --> 36:48.771
Five. All right.

36:49.140 --> 36:50.674
You can come sit down, but
you're not gonna stay down.

36:50.676 --> 36:52.175
You finish practice standing up.

36:53.177 --> 36:54.511
So, yeah,
we're gonna sit and stand.

36:55.146 --> 36:59.115
Three, two, one.
Rock... Stand.

36:59.984 --> 37:01.551
One. All right,
we'll go back down.

37:01.986 --> 37:04.354
That's one.

37:04.356 --> 37:07.157
-That's two. Okay, no hands. [laughing] All right.
-[laughs]

37:07.159 --> 37:08.291
And down.

37:09.827 --> 37:11.027
That's four.

37:11.562 --> 37:12.996
All right, hold that.
That's good.

37:13.364 --> 37:15.899
Three, two, one.

37:15.901 --> 37:18.535
That's up. That's five. All
right, stay right there. Hands up.

37:19.537 --> 37:21.571
Now we're gonna lean
slightly this way.

37:21.573 --> 37:26.042
-[chuckles] -One, two,
three, four, five. Same thing.

37:26.210 --> 37:30.080
One, two, three, four, five.

37:30.082 --> 37:31.514
All right, we're going
back down. Here we go.

37:32.817 --> 37:34.884
Right, let's go.
We can head back.

37:34.886 --> 37:36.853
-Up. Give me this and get up. Here we go. Up!
-Really?

37:36.855 --> 37:38.655
On your feet, let's go.

37:38.657 --> 37:40.590
Or you're gonna owe me
a lap around this lake.

37:40.592 --> 37:42.726
- Uh-uh. No, we ain't can't do no lap.
- Huh?

37:42.728 --> 37:46.029
Three, two, one. Let's rock.

37:46.964 --> 37:49.232
You know, we're schooling
your feet. We walking.

37:49.234 --> 37:52.802
We're gonna leave the belly.
This thing ain't got a chance.

37:52.804 --> 37:54.571
- Let's go. Pick them up.
- [laughs]

37:54.573 --> 37:56.706
- Let's go. Nope.
- Slow.

37:56.708 --> 38:00.043
- And when we get halfway I'm giving you this ball.
- No, no, no, no, no.

38:00.845 --> 38:02.946
<i>[Ontreon] You know,
that wasn't so bad</i>

38:02.948 --> 38:05.615
<i>moving my body all those ways.</i>

38:05.617 --> 38:07.817
<i>When you haven't
worked out in so long,</i>

38:07.819 --> 38:11.154
<i>it helps to remind you
how out of shape you are.</i>

38:11.689 --> 38:13.757
That's it. Come on.

38:13.759 --> 38:16.660
<i>[Ontreon] For me right now,
there's a bit of shame.</i>

38:16.662 --> 38:20.263
<i>Shame and regret that
I let myself get like this.</i>

38:20.265 --> 38:22.599
<i>Because it feels like
I have so far to go.</i>

38:24.201 --> 38:25.935
Not too shabby, sir.

38:27.171 --> 38:28.305
How you feel?

38:28.307 --> 38:32.075
- [panting] - Ha. I
think I've done my part.

38:34.178 --> 38:35.211
Sir, every day.

38:35.213 --> 38:37.747
- [panting]
- Huh?

38:37.749 --> 38:39.983
- I hear you, Charles.
- Huh? Don't try to squeeze my hand!

38:39.985 --> 38:41.751
- [laughs] If I gotta sit down.
- All right.

38:41.753 --> 38:45.822
"If I gotta sit down."
[laughs]

38:45.824 --> 38:48.124
<i>[Ontreon] I guess I'll just
take it one day at a time.</i>

38:48.126 --> 38:50.160
<i>That's all I really can do.</i>

38:52.129 --> 38:53.363
